{"type":"message","id":"b57b1672","parentId":"14eb4ab9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T02:06:08.165Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user provided their API information:\n- URL: https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding\n- API Key: J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE\n- Model: minimax-m2.5\n\nThis is a CodingPlan API endpoint. For this to work with Claude Code, I need to set:\n- ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL - the API endpoint\n- ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN - the API key\n- Possibly ANTHROPIC_MODEL - though the user mentioned minimax-m2.5\n\nLet me set this up following the solution in the screenshot. I should:\n1. Create /etc/default/openclaw with the environment variables\n2. Restart the OpenClaw gateway\n3. Verify it works\n\nSince this is an OpenAI-compatible API (CodingPlan), I need to check if Claude Code supports custom base URLs. Actually, Claude Code uses the Anthropic API by default. For custom endpoints, we might need to use the ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL variable.\n\nLet me set this up.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了！这是 CodingPlan 的 API 端点。因为是兼容 OpenAI 的格式，需要额外配置 `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL`。\n\n让我配置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d5a9a42ec7ce4a3887007867","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo 'ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding/v1\nANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE\nANTHROPIC_MODEL=minimax-m2.5' | sudo tee /etc/default/openclaw"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":14789,"output":379,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15168,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775268363008,"responseId":"chatcmpl-c5bbb17d-d548-42fe-aa01-c6396d6cecbf"}}
