{"type":"message","id":"9aedec62","parentId":"832b7850","timestamp":"2026-04-04T02:12:17.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to configure Claude Code CLI to always use minimax-m2.5 model by default, so they don't have to source the environment file every time.\n\nThere are a few ways to do this:\n1. Create a shell alias or function for `claude` that sources the env first\n2. Add the environment variables to ~/.bashrc or ~/.profile so they're loaded automatically\n3. Configure Claude Code's own config file if it supports it\n\nThe simplest way is to add the environment variables to ~/.bashrc so they're loaded on every shell session.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n最简单的方式是把环境变量写入 `~/.bashrc`，这样每次打开终端都会自动加载：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d5642968373c2bfcb0234d1cf05c9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat >> ~/.bashrc << 'EOF'\n\n# CodingPlan API 配置 (Claude Code CLI)\nexport ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=\"J99ouXWKXO8Zg5tLqv92YVsPNFhwuZc-z6z2ioeg7VE\"\nexport ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=\"https://zhenze-huhehaote.cmecloud.cn/api/coding\"\nexport ANTHROPIC_MODEL=\"minimax-m2.5\"\nEOF"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":9473,"output":255,"cacheRead":14848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775268723044,"responseId":"019d564273b179dc1977fc51eb3cf067"}}
